      • parseInitialPBSD

        private void parseInitialPBSD(ClientConnection connection)
                       throws DisconnectException
        Parse the initial PBSD - PiggyBackedSessionData code point.

        If sent by the server, it contains a PBSD_ISO code point followed by a byte representing the JDBC isolation level, and a PBSD_SCHEMA code point followed by the name of the current schema as an UTF-8 String.

        Throws:
        DisconnectException

      • parsePBSD

        void parsePBSD()
        throws DisconnectException
        Parse a PBSD - PiggyBackedSessionData code point. Can contain one or both of, a PBSD_ISO code point followed by a byte representing the jdbc isolation level, and a PBSD_SCHEMA code point followed by the name of the current schema as an UTF-8 String.
        Throws:
        DisconnectException
